{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab986da3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12205"},"text":"§ 12205.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Commissioned officers: appointment; educational requirement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab986da4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"No person may be appointed to a grade above the grade of first lieutenant in the Army Reserve, Air Force Reserve, or Marine Corps Reserve or to a grade above the grade of lieutenant (junior grade) in the Navy Reserve, or be federally recognized in a grade above the grade of first lieutenant as a member of the Army National Guard or Air National Guard, unless that person has been awarded a baccalaureate degree by a qualifying educational institution.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab986da5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exceptions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) does not apply to the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986da6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The appointment to or recognition in a higher grade of a person who is appointed in or assigned for service in a health profession for which a baccalaureate degree is not a condition of original appointment or assignment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986da7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The appointment in the Navy Reserve or Marine Corps Reserve of a person appointed for service as an officer designated as a limited duty officer.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986da8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The appointment in the Navy Reserve of a person appointed for service under the Naval Aviation Cadet (NAVCAD) program or the Seaman to Admiral program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986da9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The appointment to or recognition in a higher grade of any person who was appointed to, or federally recognized in, the grade of captain or, in the case of the Navy, lieutenant before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1995","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986daa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/b/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Recognition in the grade of captain or major in the Alaska Army National Guard of a person who resides permanently at a location in Alaska that is more than 50 miles from each of the cities of Anchorage, Fairbanks, and Juneau, Alaska, by paved road and who is serving in a Scout unit or a Scout supporting unit.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab986dab-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Qualifying Educational Institutions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986dac-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A qualifying educational institution for purposes of this section is an educational institution that is accredited or that meets the requirements of paragraph (2).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986dad-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986dae-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An unaccredited educational institution shall be considered to be a qualifying educational institution for purposes of the appointment or recognition of a person who is a graduate of that institution if the Secretary concerned determines that (as of the year of the graduation of that person from that institution) at least three educational institutions that are accredited and that maintain Reserve Officers’ Training Corps programs each generally grant baccalaureate degree credit for completion of courses of the unaccredited institution equivalent to the baccalaureate degree credit granted by the unaccredited institution for the completion of those courses.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986daf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In order to assist the Secretary concerned in making determinations under subparagraph (A), any unaccredited institution that seeks to be considered to be a qualifying educational institution for purposes of this paragraph shall submit to the Secretary of Defense each year such information as the Secretary may require concerning the program of instruction at that institution.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986db0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a person with a degree from an unaccredited institution that is a qualifying educational institution under this paragraph, the degree may not have been awarded more than eight years before the date on which the person is to be appointed to, or recognized in, the grade of captain or, in the case of the Navy Reserve, lieutenant, in order for that person to be considered for purposes of subsection (a) to have been awarded a baccalaureate degree by a qualifying educational institution.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab986db1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Waiver Authority for Army OCS Graduates and Certain Marine Corps Officers","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986db2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of the Army may waive the applicability of subsection (a) to any officer whose original appointment in the Army as a Reserve officer is through the Army Officer Candidate School program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986db3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of the Navy may waive the applicability of subsection (a) to any officer whose original appointment in the Marine Corps as a Reserve officer is through the Marine Corps meritorious commissioning program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab986db4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any such waiver shall be made on a case-by-case basis, considering the individual circumstances of the officer involved, and may continue in effect for no more than two years after the waiver is granted. The Secretary concerned may provide for such a waiver to be effective before the date of the waiver, as appropriate in an individual case.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab986db5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/484/dA/tV/s515/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–484, div. A, title V, § 515(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2406"},"text":"106 Stat. 2406","children":[],"tail":", § 596; renumbered § 12205 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tV"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title V","children":[],"tail":", §§ 519, 520, title XVI, § 1662(c)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2755"},"text":"108 Stat. 2755","children":[],"tail":", 2990; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/dA/tV"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, div. A, title V","children":[],"tail":", §§ 504, 505, title X, § 1074(a)(22), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-23"},"text":"Sept. 23, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2512"},"text":"110 Stat. 2512","children":[],"tail":", 2660; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/107/dA/tV/s512/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–107, div. A, title V, § 512(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-12-28"},"text":"Dec. 28, 2001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/1092"},"text":"115 Stat. 1092","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/dA/tV/s515/b/1/KK"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, div. A, title V, § 515(b)(1)(KK)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3234"},"text":"119 Stat. 3234","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab986db6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab986db7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idab986db8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190/dA/tV/s523"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190, div. A, title V, § 523","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-05"},"text":"Dec. 5, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1363"},"text":"105 Stat. 1363","children":[],"tail":", which was set out as a note under section 591 [now 12201] of this title, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/35/s203/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–35, § 203(a)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab986db9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsecs. (a), (b)(2), (3), (c)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Navy Reserve” for “Naval Reserve”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2001—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/107"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–107","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/s1074/a/22"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, § 1074(a)(22)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “No person” for “After "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1995","children":[],"tail":", no person”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/s505"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, § 505","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or the Seaman to Admiral program” after “(NAVCAD) program”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/s504"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, § 504","children":[],"tail":", substituted “eight years” for “three years”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1662/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1662(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s596"},"text":"section 596 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s519/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 519(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a qualifying educational institution” for “an accredited educational institution”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s520/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 520(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a person” for “an individual”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s520/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 520(a)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s519/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 519(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab986dba-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab986dbb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2001 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/107/dA/tV/s512/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–107, div. A, title V, § 512(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-12-28"},"text":"Dec. 28, 2001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/1092"},"text":"115 Stat. 1092","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/107/107/dA/tV/s512/b"},"text":"“Subsection (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12205"},"text":"section 12205 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as added by subsection (a), shall apply with respect to officers appointed before, on, or after the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-12-28"},"text":"Dec. 28, 2001","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab986dbc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Authority for Temporary Waiver for Certain Army Reserve Officers of Baccalaureate Degree Requirement for Promotion of Reserve Officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/261/dA/tV/s516"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–261, div. A, title V, § 516","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2008"},"text":"112 Stat. 2008","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/261/dA/tV/s516"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Waiver Authority for Army OCS Graduates","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of the Army may waive the applicability of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12205/a"},"text":"section 12205(a) of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, to any officer who before the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1998","children":[],"tail":"] was commissioned through the Army Officer Candidate School. Any such waiver shall be made on a case-by-case basis, considering the individual circumstances of the officer involved, and may continue in effect for no more than 2 years after the waiver is granted. The Secretary may provide for such a waiver to be effective before the date of the waiver, as appropriate in an individual case."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Expiration of Authority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A waiver under this section may not be granted after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
